The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Frontpage | Team visits district
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Team visits district
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Bhubaneswar, Sept. 2: The situation in Khandhamal continued to be volatile today, even as a high-level official team, headed by the home secretary, visited the district.        
	Former Lokpal and retired high court judge S.C. Mohapatra was appointed the head of a judicial commission that will probe into the murder of VHP leader Swami Laxmananda Saraswati and his four associates on August 23 and the subsequent clashes.        
	Home secretary T.K. Mishra, director-general of police G.C. Nanda and senior officers visited the district to review the situation and assess the damage, on the eve of the scheduled visit of Union home minister Shivraj Patil.        
	The team also visited a relief camp at Tikabali and spoke to families before attending a review meeting at Phubani, the district headquarters. Home secretary, Mishra assured all help to the riot victims.                                                                                                                                            
